  "description": "A peaceful story about a woman who discovers something unexpected during her daily walk through the park.",
  "level": "A2",
  "text": "Every morning, Sarah walks through the quiet park near her house. The air is fresh and cool. She likes to listen to the birds singing in the tall trees.\n\nToday, she notices something different. A small wooden bench sits under the oldest oak tree. It was not there yesterday. Sarah walks closer and sees a note on the bench.\n\nThe note says: \"Sit down and breathe. The world can wait.\" Sarah smiles. She sits on the bench and closes her eyes. The morning sun warms her face. She hears the gentle sound of water from the nearby fountain.\n\nAfter a few minutes, she opens her eyes. An elderly man is sitting on the other side of the bench. He nods and says, \"Beautiful morning, isn't it?\" Sarah agrees. They sit together in comfortable silence, watching the leaves dance in the breeze.\n\nSarah stands up and thanks the man. He waves and says, \"See you tomorrow.\" She laughs softly and walks home. The rest of her day feels lighter, as if the morning gave her a small gift.",
